The paper discusses the trajectory planning for a parallel robot, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and computation, which could be categorized under cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering). The paper also deals with the uniqueness of domains and characteristic surfaces, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of Jacobian matrices, which is a common tool in robotics and falls under cs.ROB (Robotics). Finally, the paper also involves the depiction of trajectories, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
